<h2>
    Travel Authorization
</h2>
<p>
    The Travel Authorization features will be based on the <a href="@Url.Content(Links.content.docs.travel_module_overview_2007_pdf)"
        target="_blank">University of Cincinnati Travel Module Proposal</a>, and are
    tentatively planned for incremental releases between March and June 2013.
</p>
<div id="feature_a_1" class="user-story-card">
    <h3>
        Request Travel Authorization
    </h3>
    <p>
        <strong>In order to</strong> plan employment-related domestic and international
        travel,
        <br />
        <strong>As an</strong> institutional employee,
        <br />
        <strong>I want to</strong> request travel authorization from my supervisor.
    </p>
</div>
<div id="feature_a_2" class="user-story-card">
    <h3>
        Approve or Deny Travel Authorization
    </h3>
    <p>
        <strong>In order to</strong> be aware when and where my employees are traveling,
        <br />
        <strong>As an</strong> employee supervisor,
        <br />
        <strong>I want to</strong> approve or deny travel authorization requests submitted
        by my employees.
    </p>
</div>
<div id="feature_a_3" class="user-story-card">
    <h3>
        Send Travel Advisory Messages
    </h3>
    <p>
        <strong>In order to</strong> reduce risk and ensure my institution's policies are
        adhered to,
        <br />
        <strong>As a</strong> institutional travel strategist,
        <br />
        <strong>I want to</strong> automatically send messages to an employee who has been
        approved for travel.
    </p>
</div>
<div id="feature_a_4" class="user-story-card">
    <h3>
        Send Emergency Alert Messages to Traveling Employees
    </h3>
    <p>
        <strong>In order to</strong> advise and protect my institution's employees during
        an emergency,
        <br />
        <strong>As a</strong> institutional travel strategist,
        <br />
        <strong>I want to</strong> automatically send messages to all employees who have
        traveled to a particular country or city.
    </p>
</div>
